      <hedline>
        <hl1>In the Jury Room</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter on July 16 issue on race praises jury for going beyond race by convicting African-American man of raping herl</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I was raped by an African-American man 16 months ago. A diverse and multiracial jury last month found him guilty in less than two hours. By delivering that verdict the jury restored my faith in our ability to see beyond color and race.</p>
        <p>Name withheld  New York</p>
      </block>
